Claims 1. Food product, characterized in that it comprises: - a meat-based layer (12), or mixture of meats-based layer, with a first side (40), a second side (41) and one or more connection edges (42) defined between said first side (40) and said second side (41); - an impermeable covering layer (13) disposed on the whole surface of said meat- based layer (12); - a layer of batter (14) that covers only said first side (40) and at least part of said connection edges (42) of said meat-based layer (12); - a breaded layer (15) distributed on at least part said layer of batter (14). 2. Food product according to claim 1, characterized in that it also comprises a garnish (16) distributed on at least part of the surface of said meat-based layer (12) covered with said impermeable covering layer (13) and left uncovered by said layer of batter ( 14) and said breaded layer (15). 3. Food product according to claim 1 or 2, characterized in that said meat- based layer (12) comprises one or more types of meat, to which also other elements and/or stabilizers have been added, and has a thickness comprised between 2mm and 10mm, preferably comprised between 3mm and 6mm. 4. Food product according to any preceding claims, characterized in that said impermeable covering layer (13) consists of an impermeable covering mixture (25) comprising water and protein and/or starch, said protein and/or starch being contained in said covering mixture (25) for a quantity comprised between 6% and 40% of the total quantity of said covering mixture (25). 5. Food product according to any preceding claims, characterized in that the batter (29) of said layer of batter (14) has a ratio of dry ingredients to water comprised between 1 :2 and 1 :3.5. 6. Food product according to any preceding claims, characterized in that the combination of said breaded layer (15) and said layer of batter (14) is comprised between 5% and 40% of the total weight of said food product (10). 7. Apparatus to make a food product disclosed in any claim from 1 to 6, characterized in that it comprises: - a meat taking station (17), configured to take meat, or a mixture of one or more types of meat, from one or more containers (19); 

 - a molding station (21) to mold a meat-based layer (12), configured to shape said meat-based layer (12) with a first side (40) facing downward, a second side (41) facing upward and one or more connection edges (42) defined between said first side (40) and said second side (41); - a covering station (23) to cover said meat-based layer (12), configured to distribute an impermeable covering mixture (25) over the whole surface of said meat-based layer (12) in order to obtain an impermeable covering layer (13); - a breading preparation station (27), configured to distribute a layer of batter (14) only on said first side (40), facing downward, and at least part of the connection edges (42) of said meat-based layer (12); - a breading station (30), configured to distribute shredded ingredients on at least part of said layer of batter (14) until a breaded layer (15) is obtained; - a frying station (32), configured to fry said food product (10), keeping said breaded layer (15) facing downward; - a cooking station (34) in an oven (35), configured to finish the cooking of said meat-based layer (12), keeping said breaded layer (15) facing upward. 8. Apparatus according to claim 7, characterized in that it comprises: - a garnishing station (38), also remote, configured to distribute the ingredients of said garnish (16) at least on part of the surface of said meat-based layer (12) covered with said impermeable covering layer (13) and left uncovered by said layer of batter (14) and said breaded layer (15); - a freezing station (37), configured to freeze said food product (10) after cooking in said oven (35) or after having been garnished. 9. Apparatus according to claim 7 or 8, characterized in that said breading preparation station (27) comprises a batter delivering device (28) disposed below said food product (10) being worked, said batter delivering device (28) being configured to distribute a batter (29) from down onto said first side (40) facing downward and at least part of said connection edges (42) of said food product (10) being worked, until a layer of batter (14) is obtained. 10. Apparatus according to any claim from 7 to 9, characterized in that it comprises a flattening station (45) configured to bring said meat-based layer ( 12) to the target thickness and to assure its target shape and size. 1 1. Method to obtain a food product as disclosed in the claims 1 to 6 and/or 

 using an apparatus as described in the claims 7 to 10, characterized in that it comprises: - a step of taking meat or a mixture of meats; - a step of molding said meat or mixture of meats to define a meat-based layer (12) with a first side (40) facing downward, a second side (41) facing upward and one or more connection edges (42) defined between said first side (40) and said second side (41); - a step of covering the whole surface of said meat-based layer (12) with an impermeable covering mixture (25); - a step of distributing a batter (29) only on said first side (40), facing downward, and at least part of said connection edges (42) of said meat-based layer (12) until a layer of batter (14) is obtained; - a breading step during which a combination of shredded ingredients are distributed at least on said layer of batter (14) until a breaded layer (15) is obtained; - a frying step keeping said breaded layer (15) facing downward; - a cooking step in an oven (35) reaching a temperature inside said meat-based layer (12) higher than 75Â°C and keeping said breaded layer (15) facing upward. 12. Method according to claim 1 1, characterized in that it comprises a garnishing step during which one or more ingredients are distributed at least on part of the surface of said meat-based layer (12), covered with said impermeable covering layer (13) and left uncovered by said layer of batter (14) and said breaded layer (15). 13. Method according to claim 1 1 or 12, characterized in that said step of distributing a batter (29) provides that said batter (29) is distributed only on said first side (40), facing downward, and at least part of said connection edges (42) of said meat-based layer (12). 14. Method according to any claim from 1 1 to 13, characterized in that it provides that said molding step is combined with a step of flattening during which said meat-based layer (12) is brought to the target thickness, shape and size.
